Package qualitypatternmodel.graphstructure

Interface SingleElement

  • All Superinterfaces:
    qualitypatternmodel.graphstructure.Comparable, qualitypatternmodel.graphstructure.Element, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, qualitypatternmodel.patternstructure.PatternElement
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SingleElementImpl
    public interface SingleElement
extends qualitypatternmodel.graphstructure.Element
    A representation of the model object 'Single Element'.

    The following features are supported:

    • Mapping To
    • Mapping From
    • Root
    • Next Single
    • Previous
    • Next Set
    See Also:

      • copyNextElementsToNextGraphs

        void copyNextElementsToNextGraphs()
                           throws qualitypatternmodel.exceptions.MissingPatternContainerException
        Copies all contained SingleElement objects to the next graphs. Corresponding SingleElement objects are created in these graphs and SingleElementMapping objects are added to the morphism.
        Throws:
        qualitypatternmodel.exceptions.MissingPatternContainerException

      • copyNextElementToNextGraphs

        void copyNextElementToNextGraphs​(SingleElement nextElement)
                          throws qualitypatternmodel.exceptions.MissingPatternContainerException
        Copies the contained SingleElement nextElement to the next graphs. A corresponding SingleElement object is created in these graphs and a SingleElementMapping object is added to the morphism.
        Parameters:
        the - SingleElement to be copied.
        Throws:
        qualitypatternmodel.exceptions.MissingPatternContainerException

      • removeElementFromPreviousGraphs

        void removeElementFromPreviousGraphs()
        Removes SingleElement objects in previous graphs which are directly or transitively connected to this via a SingleElementMapping.

      • copyNextElementToPreviousGraphs

        void copyNextElementToPreviousGraphs​(SingleElement nextElement,
                                     boolean recursive)
        Copies the contained SingleElement nextElement to the previous graph or recursively all previous graphs in case recursive is true. A corresponding SingleElement object is created in these graphs and a SingleElementMapping object is added to the morphism.
        Parameters:
        nextElement - the SingleElement to be copied
        recursive - if true, the object is copied recursively to all previous graphs

      • copyNextElementsToPreviousGraphs

        void copyNextElementsToPreviousGraphs​(boolean recursive)
        Copies all contained SingleElement objects to the previous graph or recursively all previous graphs in case recursive is true. Corresponding SingleElement objects are created in these graphs and SingleElementMapping objects are added to the morphism.
        Parameters:
        recursive - if true, the objects are copied recursively to all previous graphs
